<subSubSection pageId="42" pageNumber="523" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="42.[79,1035,981,1420]" pageId="42" pageNumber="523">
<emphasis box="[120,385,981,1005]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="523">Diagnosis. Petalomona s</emphasis>
, rigid, 15±24 Mm long, dorso-ventrall y ¯attened, hyaline body with one emergent ¯agellum, without grooves or ridges.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[79,1035,981,1420]" pageId="42" pageNumber="523">
<emphasis box="[120,253,1046,1069]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="523">Description.</emphasis>
Cell outline ovate, 15±24 Mm long, 5±10 Mm wide, rigid, dorsoventrally ¯attened. Cells are rather hyaline. There are no grooves and no ridges on either side of the cell. Most cells have a pointed posterior end but some cells have a rounded posterior end. Small and large granules occupy the entire cell except at the poles. One ¯agellum emerges from the canal and is slightly shorter than the cell. The reservoir is situated subapically in the midline of the cell. Cells move by gliding with the ¯agellum in close contact with the substratum. Often common.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[79,1035,981,1420]" pageId="42" pageNumber="523">
<emphasis box="[120,226,1268,1292]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="523">Remarks.</emphasis>
We assign this species to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="S.F.N.Stein" authorityYear="1859" box="[551,692,1268,1292]" class="Imbricatea" family="Thaumatomonadidae" genus="Petalomonas" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Thaumatomonadida" pageId="42" pageNumber="523" phylum="Cercozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[551,692,1268,1292]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="523">Petalomonas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because it is a rigid gliding heterotrophic euglenid with one emergent ¯agellum. This species is easily distinguished from most species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="S.F.N.Stein" authorityYear="1859" box="[388,529,1332,1356]" class="Imbricatea" family="Thaumatomonadidae" genus="Petalomonas" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Thaumatomonadida" pageId="42" pageNumber="523" phylum="Cercozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[388,529,1332,1356]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="523">Petalomonas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its hyaline body and smooth cell surface. It is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Christen, 1962" authorityName="Christen" authorityYear="1962" box="[326,624,1364,1388]" class="Archamoebea" family="Pelomyxidae" genus="Mastigella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Pelobiontida" pageId="42" pageNumber="523" phylum="Amoebozoa" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis box="[326,446,1364,1388]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="523">P. simplex</emphasis>
Christen, 
<quantity box="[571,624,1364,1388]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.98348" pageId="42" pageNumber="523" unit="in" value="1962.0">1962</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in general appearance and hyaline body, but 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Christen" authorityYear="1962" box="[200,318,1396,1420]" class="Archamoebea" family="Pelomyxidae" genus="Mastigella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Pelobiontida" pageId="42" pageNumber="523" phylum="Amoebozoa" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis box="[200,318,1396,1420]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="523">P. simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is slightly larger (27.5±31 Mm) (see 
<bibRefCitation author="CHRISTEN, H. R." box="[728,908,1396,1420]" pageId="42" pageNumber="523" pagination="202" refId="ref39564" refString="CHRISTEN, H. R., 1962 b, Neue oder weing bekannte Eugleninen und Volvocalen, Revue Algologie, new series, 6, 162 ± 202." type="journal article" year="1962">Christen, 1962b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
